    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on ‘</span><span class=\"english\">Potential Health Hazards of Adolescents</span><span class=\"english\">’</span><span class=\"english\"> within 10 sentences.</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Potential Health Hazards of Adolescents</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Adolescence is a stage of life filled with energy, growth, and change, but it also brings several potential health hazards. During this period, many young people face peer pressure to use alcohol, cigarettes, or other harmful substances. Such habits can cause long-term damage to physical health and increase the risk of addiction. Another serious hazard is the early involvement in unsafe sexual activities, which may lead to unintended pregnancies and sexually transmitted infections such as HIV. Mental health issues, including stress, depression, and anxiety, also become common because of academic pressure and social expectations. Lack of proper nutrition and irregular lifestyles may further weaken their health. Injuries from risky behaviors like reckless driving or unsafe sports are also frequent. These hazards show that adolescence is not only a time of growth but also of vulnerability. Awareness, guidance, and proper care can reduce these risks. Responsible adults must therefore play a vital role.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------09 Marks </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Potential Health Hazards of Adolescents</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> --------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Adolescence is a period of growth, change, and energy, but it also presents several potential health risks.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Adolescent Health Hazards</span><span class=\"english\">) (Any 06) </span><span class=\"english\">--------------------------06 Marks                                                                                       </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Teenagers often face peer pressure to try alcohol, cigarettes, or harmful substances.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">These habits can cause long-term physical damage and lead to addiction.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Early involvement in unsafe sexual activities can result in unwanted pregnancies and sexually transmitted infections.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Mental health problems like stress, depression, and anxiety are common due to academic and social pressure.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Poor nutrition and irregular lifestyles can harm overall health.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Risky behaviors such as reckless driving or unsafe sports often lead to injuries.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Adolescence is a period of both growth and vulnerability, requiring care and guidance.</span></p><p><span> </span><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------01 Mark </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Responsible adults play a crucial role in reducing risks through awareness, guidance, and proper care.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para)</span><span class=\"english\">.</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Make meaningful sentences with each of the following words.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Accord, Tremendous, Integrity, Repetitiously, Exert</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Accord (</span><span class=\"english\">Noun )</span><span class=\"english\"> = </span><span class=\"english\">International </span><span class=\"english\">accords</span><span class=\"english\"> can lead to lasting peace and cooperation among nations.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Accord (</span><span class=\"english\">Verb )</span><span class=\"english\"> = Our society accords great importance to the family. [Students can use it both as Noun and Verb]</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Tremendous = </span><span class=\"english\">The </span><span class=\"english\">tremendous</span><span class=\"english\"> success of the event surprised everyone.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Integrity = He earned respect through </span><span class=\"english\">integrity</span><span class=\"english\"> and fairness in difficult situations. </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Repetitiously = The clock ticked </span><span class=\"english\">repetitiously</span><span class=\"english\">, creating a monotonous background for study.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Exert = Athletes must </span><span class=\"english\">exert</span><span class=\"english\"> great energy to achieve victory in competitions.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\"> Instructions: </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">i</span><span class=\"english\">)</span><span class=\"english\"> Any correct and logically meaningful sentence will be accepted. (Sentences with weak meaning will not be allowed.)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For any grammatical or structural mistake, full marks have to be deducted. Examiners have to show and correct the mistake(s) in the scripts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(iii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For </span><span class=\"english\">02</span><span class=\"english\"> spelling mistakes, </span><span class=\"english\">01 mark</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted, for 01 spelling mistake, </span><span class=\"english\">0.5 marks</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted from that very sentence.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">(iv)</span><span class=\"english\"> For changing the part of speech of the given word by adding a </span><span class=\"english\">suffix or prefix</span><span class=\"english\">, the full marks have to be deducted from the very number. But students can use any form if the given word is a verb (depending on the </span><span class=\"english\">subject-verb agreement, tense, person, number</span><span class=\"english\">, etc.).</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎Comment: </span><span class=\"english\">Use the given word without changing its parts of speech</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Read the text below and fill in the gaps with the clues given in the box. There are more words than necessary. Make any grammatical changes (if necessary).</span></p><p><span><img src=\"images/Varsity_Kha_Weekly_Live_Exam-09_Set_2_25c33eb2.png\"/></span></p><p><span class=\"english\">At daylight I was (a) _____ wakened by the sound of chopping. </span><span class=\"english\">Again</span><span class=\"english\"> it was so even in texture that I went back to sleep. When I left my bed in the cool morning, the boy had come and gone, and a stack of kindling was neat (b)____the cabin wall. He came after school in the afternoon and worked until time to return to the orphanage. His name was Jerry.... he had been at the orphanage (c)____he was four. I could picture him at four, with the same grave gray-blue eyes and the same – independence? No, the word that comes to me is (d)____. It is bedded on courage, but it is more than brave. It is honest, but it is more than honesty. The ax </span><span class=\"english\">handle</span><span class=\"english\"> broke one day. Jerry said the woodshop at the orphanage would repair it. I brought money to pay for the job and he (e)____it.</span></p>",
